org.team5940.robot_core.modules.control.procedures

Interface ProcedureModule

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Module, OwnableModule, java.lang.Runnable
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractProcedureModule, AggregateProcedureModule, ContinuousSelectableProcedureModule, MultipleTestRunnerProcedureModule, SelectableMJPEGStreamerModule, SingleShotSelectableProcedureModule

    public interface ProcedureModule
extends OwnableModule, java.lang.Runnable
    A ProcedureModule is a small, iterative snippet of code. A ProcedureModule should only be run once at a time by a particular thread, either concurrently to other code by acquiring this and it's dependencies and then calling the start, update and clean methods manually or by using the run methods.

      • run

        default void run(boolean forceAcquisition,
                 long delay)
        Acquires this and this' extended dependencies, then runs the procedure to completion or premature, external clean. Catches any exceptions internally.
        Parameters:
        forceAcquisition - Whether to force acquisition of this and this' extended dependencies.
        delay - The number of milliseconds to wait between calls to updateProcedure() while running.

      • updateProcedure

        boolean updateProcedure()
                 throws ThreadUnauthorizedException,
                        java.lang.IllegalStateException
        Updates the procedure if it has been started. This should catch any exceptions internally and then return true if fatal. It may be called after a previous call returned true but before this has been cleaned.
        Returns:
        True if the procedure has finished updating (or errored, any other reason it's done), false otherwise.
        Throws:
        ThreadUnauthorizedException - Thrown if this is not accessible to the current thread.
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - Thrown if this has not been started.

      • cleanProcedure

        void cleanProcedure()
             throws ThreadUnauthorizedException
        Cleans the procedure, this resets the procedure so that it is ready to be started. Should be called if the procedure has finished updating or you want to terminate it prematurely. May be called even if this is already ready to be started.
        Throws:
        ThreadUnauthorizedException - Thrown if this is not accessible to the current thread.

      • isReadyToStart

        boolean isReadyToStart()
        Gets whether this can be started.
        Returns:
